dataIdInfo.idAbs: The 52 congressional districts within the State of California represent the geographically defined territories used for electing members to the U.S. House of Representatives. The current U.S. Congressional boundaries in California were approved by the California Citizens Redistricting Commission in 2021 following the completion of the 2020 United States Census.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: US Congressional Districts in California approved by the 2020 California Citizens Redistricting Commission
